  <Name>k__BackingField: Lamentations
  fancyName: 
  nickname: lam
  version: {fileID: 11400000, guid: bd3f8ba6a2445b646991a3e44f7f687a, type: 2}
  description: 
  chapters:
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  How doth the city sit solitary,  <i>That was</i> full of people! 
        <i>How</i> is she become as a widow!She <i>that was</i> great among the nations, 
        <i>And</i> princess among the provinces,  <i>How</i> is she become tributary!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'She weepeth sore in the night,And her tears <i>are</i> on her cheeks:Among
        all her loversShe hath none to comfort <i>her:</i>All her friends have dealt
        treacherously with her,They are become her enemies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Judah is gone into captivity because of affliction,And because of
        great servitude:She dwelleth among the heathen,She findeth no rest:All her
        persecutors overtook herBetween the straits.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The ways of Zion do mourn,Because none come to the solemn feasts:All
        her gates are desolate:Her priests sigh,Her virgins are afflicted,And she
        <i>is</i> in bitterness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Her adversaries are the chief,Her enemies prosper;For the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath afflicted herFor the multitude of her transgressions:Her children are
        goneInto captivity before the enemy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And from the daughter of ZionAll her beauty is departed:Her princes
        are become like harts  <i>That</i> find no pasture,And they are gone without
        strengthBefore the pursuer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Jerusalem rememberedIn the days of her affliction and of her miseriesAll
        her pleasant thingsThat she had in the days of old,When her people fell into
        the hand of the enemy,And none did help her:The adversaries saw her,  <i>And</i>
        did mock at her sabbaths.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Jerusalem hath grievously sinned;Therefore she is removed:All that
        honoured her despise her,Because they have seen her nakedness:Yea, she sigheth,And
        turneth backward.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Her filthiness <i>is</i> in her skirts;She remembereth not her last
        end;Therefore she came down wonderfully:She had no comforter.O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,
        behold my affliction:For the enemy hath magnified <i>himself</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The adversary hath spread out his handUpon all her pleasant things:For
        she hath seen <i>that</i> the heathenEntered into her sanctuary,Whom thou
        didst command  <i>That</i> they should not enter into thy congregation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'All her people sigh,They seek bread;They have given their pleasant
        thingsFor meat to relieve the soul:See, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and
        consider;For I am become vile.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: '  <i>Is it</i> nothing to you,All ye that pass by?Behold, and see
        if there be any sorrowLike unto my sorrow, which is done unto me,Wherewith
        the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath afflicted  <i>Me</i> in the day of his
        fierce anger.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'From above hath he sent fire into my bones,And it prevaileth against
        them:He hath spread a net for my feet,He hath turned me back:He hath made
        me desolate  <i>And</i> faint all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The yoke of my transgressions is boundBy his hand:They are wreathed,
        <i>and</i> come up upon my neck:He hath made my strength to fall,The Lord
        hath delivered me into <i>their</i> hands,  <i>From whom</i> I am not able
        to rise up.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The Lord hath trodden under foot all my mighty <i>men</i>In the midst
        of me:He hath called an assembly against meTo crush my young men:The Lord
        hath trodden the virgin,The daughter of Judah, <i>as</i> in a winepress.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'For these <i>things</i> I weep;Mine eye, mine eye runneth down with
        water,Because the comforter that should relieve mySoul is far from me:My
        children are desolate,Because the enemy prevailed.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'Zion spreadeth forth her hands,  <i>And there is</i> none to comfort
        her:The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath commanded concerning Jacob,  <i>That</i>
        his adversaries <i>should be</i> round about him:Jerusalem is asA menstruous
        woman among them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> is righteous;For I have rebelled
        against his commandment:Hear, I pray you, all people,And behold my sorrow:My
        virgins and my young menAre gone into captivity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'I called for my lovers,  <i>But</i> they deceived me:My priests and
        mine eldersGave up the ghost in the city,While they sought their meatTo relieve
        their souls.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Behold, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>; for I <i>am</i> in distress:My
        bowels are troubled;Mine heart is turned within me;For I have grievously
        rebelled:Abroad the sword bereaveth,At home <i>there is</i> as death.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'They have heard that I sigh:  <i>There is</i> none to comfort me:All
        mine enemies have heard of my trouble;They are glad that thou hast done <i>it:</i>Thou
        wilt bring the day <i>that</i> thou hast called,And they shall be like unto
        me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Let all their wickedness come before thee;And do unto them,As thou
        hast done unto meFor all my transgressions:For my sighs <i>are</i> many,And
        my heart <i>is</i> faint.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  How hath the Lord coveredThe daughter of Zion with a cloud in his
        anger,  <i>And</i> cast down from heaven unto the earthThe beauty of Israel,And
        remembered not his footstoolIn the day of his anger!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The Lord hath swallowed upAll the habitations of Jacob, and hath
        not pitied:He hath thrown down in his wrathThe strong holds of the daughter
        of Judah;He hath brought <i>them</i> down to the ground:He hath polluted
        the kingdom and the princes thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'He hath cut off in <i>his</i> fierce angerAll the horn of Israel:He
        hath drawn back his right handFrom before the enemy,And he burned against
        Jacob like a flaming fire,  <i>Which</i> devoureth round about.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'He hath bent his bow like an enemy:He stood with his right hand as
        an adversary,And slew all <i>that were</i> pleasant to the eyeIn the tabernacle
        of the daughter of Zion:He poured out his fury like fire.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'The Lord was as an enemy:He hath swallowed up Israel,He hath swallowed
        up all her palaces:He hath destroyed his strong holds,And hath increased
        in the daughter of JudahMourning and lamentation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'And he hath violently taken away his tabernacle, as <i>if it were
        of</i> a garden:He hath destroyed his places of the assembly:The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>
        hath caused the solemn feastsAnd sabbaths to be forgotten in Zion,And hath
        despised in the indignation of his angerThe king and the priest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'The Lord hath cast off his altar,He hath abhorred his sanctuary,He
        hath given up into the hand of the enemyThe walls of her palaces;They have
        made a noise in the house of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,As in the day
        of a solemn feast.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath purposed to destroyThe wall
        of the daughter of Zion:He hath stretched out a line,He hath not withdrawn
        his hand from destroying:Therefore he made the rampart and the wall to lament;They
        languished together.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'Her gates are sunk into the ground;He hath destroyed and broken her
        bars:Her king and her princes <i>are</i> among the Gentiles:The law <i>is</i>
        no <i>more</i>;Her prophets also findNo vision from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The elders of the daughter of ZionSit upon the ground, <i>and</i>
        keep silence:They have cast up dust upon their heads;They have girded themselves
        with sackcloth:The virgins of JerusalemHang down their heads to the ground.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'Mine eyes do fail with tears,My bowels are troubled,My liver is poured
        upon the earth,For the destruction of the daughter of my people;Because the
        children and the sucklings swoonIn the streets of the city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'They say to their mothers,Where <i>is</i> corn and wine?When they
        swooned as the woundedIn the streets of the city,When their soul was poured
        outInto their mothers'' bosom.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'What thing shall I take to witness for thee? what thing shall I liken
        to thee,O daughter of Jerusalem?What shall I equal to thee, that I may comfort
        thee,O virgin daughter of Zion?For thy breach <i>is</i> great like the sea:Who
        can heal thee?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'Thy prophets have seen vainAnd foolish things for thee:And they have
        not discovered thine iniquity,To turn away thy captivity;But have seen for
        thee false burdensAnd causes of banishment.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'All that pass by clap  <i>Their</i> hands at thee;They hiss and wag
        their headAt the daughter of Jerusalem, <i>saying</i>,  <i>Is</i> this the
        city that <i>men</i> callThe perfection of beauty,The joy of the whole earth?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'All thine enemiesHave opened their mouth against thee:They hiss and
        gnash the teeth:They say, We have swallowed <i>her</i> up:Certainly this
        <i>is</i> the day that we looked for;We have found, we have seen <i>it</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath done <i>that</i> which he had
        devised;He hath fulfilled his wordThat he had commanded in the days of old:He
        hath thrown down, and hath not pitied:And he hath caused <i>thine</i> enemy
        to rejoice over thee,He hath set up the horn of thine adversaries.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Their heart cried unto the Lord,O wall of the daughter of Zion,Let
        tears run down like a riverDay and night:Give thyself no rest;Let not the
        apple of thine eye cease.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Arise, cry out in the night:In the beginning of the watchesPour out
        thine heart like waterBefore the face of the Lord:Lift up thy hands toward
        him for the lifeOf thy young children,That faint for hungerIn the top of
        every street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Behold, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,And consider to whom thou hast
        done this.Shall the women eat their fruit,  <i>And</i> children of a span
        long?Shall the priest and the prophet be slainIn the sanctuary of the Lord?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'The young and the old lieOn the ground in the streets:My virgins
        and my young menAre fallen by the sword;Thou hast slain <i>them</i> in the
        day of thine anger;Thou hast killed, <i>and</i> not pitied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: Thou hast called as in a solemn dayMy terrors round about,So that
        in the day of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>'s angerNone escaped nor remained:Those
        that I have swaddled and brought up hathMine enemy consumed.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  I <i>am</i> the man <i>that</i> hath seen afflictionBy the rod
        of his wrath.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'He hath led me, and brought <i>me</i>  <i>Into</i> darkness, but
        not <i>into</i> light.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Surely against me is he turned; he turneth his hand  <i>Against me</i>
        all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'My flesh and my skin hath he made old;He hath broken my bones.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'He hath builded against me,And compassed <i>me</i> with gall and
        travail.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'He hath set me in dark places,As <i>they that be</i> dead of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'He hath hedged me about, that I cannot get out:He hath made my chain
        heavy.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Also when I cry and shout,He shutteth out my prayer.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'He hath inclosed my ways with hewn stone,He hath made my paths crooked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'He <i>was</i> unto me <i>as</i> a bear lying in wait,  <i>And as</i>
        a lion in secret places.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'He hath turned aside my ways, and pulled me in pieces:He hath made
        me desolate.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'He hath bent his bow, and set meAs a mark for the arrow.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'He hath caused the arrows of his quiverTo enter into my reins.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'I was a derision to all my people;  <i>And</i> their song all the
        day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'He hath filled me with bitterness,He hath made me drunken with wormwood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'He hath also broken my teeth with gravel stones,He hath covered me
        with ashes.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'And thou hast removed my soul far off from peace:I forgat prosperity.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'And I said, My strength and my hopeIs perished from the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Remembering mine affliction and my misery,The wormwood and the gall.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'My soul hath <i>them</i> still in remembrance,And is humbled in me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'This I recall to my mind,Therefore have I hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: '  <i>It is of</i> the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>''s mercies that
        we are not consumed,Because his compassions fail not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '23: '
      title: 
      number: 23
      content: '  <i>They are</i> new every morning:Great <i>is</i> thy faithfulness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '24: '
      title: 
      number: 24
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> my portion, saith my soul;Therefore
        will I hope in him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '25: '
      title: 
      number: 25
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>  <i>is</i> good unto them that wait
        for him,To the soul <i>that</i> seeketh him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '26: '
      title: 
      number: 26
      content: '  <i>It is</i> good that <i>a man</i> should both hope and quietlyWait
        for the salvation of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '27: '
      title: 
      number: 27
      content: '  <i>It is</i> good for a man that he bearThe yoke in his youth.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '28: '
      title: 
      number: 28
      content: 'He sitteth alone and keepeth silence,Because he hath borne <i>it</i>
        upon him.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '29: '
      title: 
      number: 29
      content: 'He putteth his mouth in the dust;If so be there may be hope.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '30: '
      title: 
      number: 30
      content: 'He giveth <i>his</i> cheek to him that smiteth him:He is filled full
        with reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '31: '
      title: 
      number: 31
      content: 'For the Lord will notCast off for ever:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '32: '
      title: 
      number: 32
      content: 'But though he cause grief, yet will he have compassionAccording to
        the multitude of his mercies.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '33: '
      title: 
      number: 33
      content: 'For he doth not afflict willinglyNor grieve the children of men.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '34: '
      title: 
      number: 34
      content: 'To crush under his feetAll the prisoners of the earth,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '35: '
      title: 
      number: 35
      content: 'To turn aside the right of a manBefore the face of the Most High,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '36: '
      title: 
      number: 36
      content: 'To subvert a man in his cause,The Lord approveth not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '37: '
      title: 
      number: 37
      content: 'Who <i>is</i> he <i>that</i> saith, and it cometh to pass,  <i>When</i>
        the Lord commandeth <i>it</i> not?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '38: '
      title: 
      number: 38
      content: 'Out of the mouth of the Most HighProceedeth not evil and good?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '39: '
      title: 
      number: 39
      content: 'Wherefore doth a living man complain,A man for the punishment of
        his sins?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '40: '
      title: 
      number: 40
      content: 'Let us search and try our ways,And turn again to the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '41: '
      title: 
      number: 41
      content: 'Let us lift up our heart with <i>our</i> handsUnto God in the heavens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '42: '
      title: 
      number: 42
      content: 'We have transgressed and have rebelled:Thou hast not pardoned.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '43: '
      title: 
      number: 43
      content: 'Thou hast covered with anger, and persecuted us:Thou hast slain,
        thou hast not pitied.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '44: '
      title: 
      number: 44
      content: 'Thou hast covered thyself with a cloud,That <i>our</i> prayer should
        not pass through.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '45: '
      title: 
      number: 45
      content: 'Thou hast made us <i>as</i> the offscouring and refuseIn the midst
        of the people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '46: '
      title: 
      number: 46
      content: 'All our enemiesHave opened their mouths against us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '47: '
      title: 
      number: 47
      content: 'Fear and a snare is come upon us,Desolation and destruction.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '48: '
      title: 
      number: 48
      content: 'Mine eye runneth down with rivers of waterFor the destruction of
        the daughter of my people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '49: '
      title: 
      number: 49
      content: 'Mine eye trickleth down, and ceaseth not,Without any intermission,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '50: '
      title: 
      number: 50
      content: 'Till the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> look down,And behold from heaven.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '51: '
      title: 
      number: 51
      content: 'Mine eye affecteth mine heartBecause of all the daughters of my city.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '52: '
      title: 
      number: 52
      content: 'Mine enemies chased me sore, like a bird,Without cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '53: '
      title: 
      number: 53
      content: 'They have cut off my life in the dungeon,And cast a stone upon me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '54: '
      title: 
      number: 54
      content: 'Waters flowed over mine head;  <i>Then</i> I said, I am cut off.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '55: '
      title: 
      number: 55
      content: 'I called upon thy name, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,Out of the
        low dungeon.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '56: '
      title: 
      number: 56
      content: 'Thou hast heard my voice:Hide not thine ear at my breathing, at my
        cry.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '57: '
      title: 
      number: 57
      content: 'Thou drewest near in the day <i>that</i> I called upon thee:Thou
        saidst, Fear not.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '58: '
      title: 
      number: 58
      content: 'O Lord, thou hast pleaded the causes of my soul;Thou hast redeemed
        my life.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '59: '
      title: 
      number: 59
      content: 'O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, thou hast seen my wrong:Judge thou
        my cause.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '60: '
      title: 
      number: 60
      content: 'Thou hast seen all their vengeance  <i>And</i> all their imaginations
        against me.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '61: '
      title: 
      number: 61
      content: 'Thou hast heard their reproach, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,  <i>And</i>
        all their imaginations against me;  '
      comments: []
    - name: '62: '
      title: 
      number: 62
      content: 'The lips of those that rose up against me,And their device against
        me all the day.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '63: '
      title: 
      number: 63
      content: 'Behold their sitting down, and their rising up;I <i>am</i> their
        musick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '64: '
      title: 
      number: 64
      content: 'Render unto them a recompence, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,According
        to the work of their hands.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '65: '
      title: 
      number: 65
      content: 'Give them sorrow of heart,Thy curse unto them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '66: '
      title: 
      number: 66
      content: Persecute and destroy them in angerFrom under the heavens of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  How is the gold become dim!  <i>How</i> is the most fine gold changed!The
        stones of the sanctuary are poured outIn the top of every street.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'The precious sons of Zion,Comparable to fine gold,How are they esteemed
        as earthen pitchers,The work of the hands of the potter!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'Even the sea monsters draw out the breast,They give suck to their
        young ones:The daughter of my people <i>is become</i> cruel,Like the ostriches
        in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'The tongue of the sucking child cleavethTo the roof of his mouth
        for thirst:The young children ask bread,  <i>And</i> no man breaketh <i>it</i>
        unto them.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'They that did feed delicatelyAre desolate in the streets:They that
        were brought upIn scarlet embrace dunghills.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'For the punishment of the iniquity of the daughter of my people is
        greaterThan the punishment of the sin of Sodom,That was overthrown as in
        a moment,And no hands stayed on her.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Her Nazarites were purer than snow,They were whiter than milk,They
        were more ruddy in body than rubies,Their polishing <i>was</i> of sapphire:  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Their visage is blacker than a coal;They are not known in the streets:Their
        skin cleaveth to their bones;It is withered, it is become like a stick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: '  <i>They that be</i> slain with the swordAre better than <i>they
        that be</i> slain with hunger:For these pine away, strickenThrough for <i>want
        of</i> the fruits of the field.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'The hands of the pitiful womenHave sodden their own children:They
        were their meatIn the destruction of the daughter of my people.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'The <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath accomplished his fury;He hath
        poured out his fierce anger,And hath kindled a fire in Zion,And it hath devoured
        the foundations thereof.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'The kings of the earth,And all the inhabitants of the world, would
        not have believedThat the adversary and the enemy should have enteredInto
        the gates of Jerusalem.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'For the sins of her prophets,  <i>And</i> the iniquities of her priests,That
        have shed the bloodOf the just in the midst of her,  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'They have wandered <i>as</i> blind <i>men</i> in the streets,They
        have polluted themselves with blood,So that men could not touchTheir garments.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'They cried unto them, Depart ye; <i>it is</i> unclean;Depart, depart,
        touch not:When they fled away and wandered,They said among the heathen,They
        shall no more sojourn <i>there</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The anger of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps> hath divided them;He
        will no more regard them:They respected not the persons of the priests,They
        favoured not the elders.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'As for us, our eyes as yet failedFor our vain help:In our watching
        we have watchedFor a nation <i>that</i> could not save <i>us</i>.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'They hunt our steps,That we cannot go in our streets:Our end is near,
        our days are fulfilled;For our end is come.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Our persecutors are swifterThan the eagles of the heaven:They pursued
        us upon the mountains,They laid wait for us in the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'The breath of our nostrils, the anointed of the <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>,Was
        taken in their pits,Of whom we said, Under his shadowWe shall live among
        the heathen.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Rejoice and be glad, O daughter of Edom,That dwellest in the land
        of Uz;The cup also shall pass through unto thee:Thou shalt be drunken, and
        shalt make thyself naked.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: The punishment of thine iniquity is accomplished, O daughter of Zion;He
        will no more carry thee away into captivity:He will visit thine iniquity,
        O daughter of Edom;He will discover thy sins.
      comments: []
  - verses:
    - name: '1: '
      title: 
      number: 1
      content: '  Remember, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, what is come upon us:Consider,
        and behold our reproach.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '2: '
      title: 
      number: 2
      content: 'Our inheritance is turned to strangers,Our houses to aliens.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '3: '
      title: 
      number: 3
      content: 'We are orphans and fatherless,Our mothers <i>are</i> as widows.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '4: '
      title: 
      number: 4
      content: 'We have drunken our water for money;Our wood is sold unto us.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '5: '
      title: 
      number: 5
      content: 'Our necks <i>are</i> under persecution:We labour, <i>and</i> have
        no rest.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '6: '
      title: 
      number: 6
      content: 'We have given the hand <i>to</i> the Egyptians,  <i>And to</i> the
        Assyrians, to be satisfied with bread.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '7: '
      title: 
      number: 7
      content: 'Our fathers have sinned, and <i>are</i> not;And we have borne their
        iniquities.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '8: '
      title: 
      number: 8
      content: 'Servants have ruled over us:  <i>There is</i> none that doth deliver
        <i>us</i> out of their hand.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '9: '
      title: 
      number: 9
      content: 'We gat our bread with <i>the peril of</i> our livesBecause of the
        sword of the wilderness.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '10: '
      title: 
      number: 10
      content: 'Our skin was black like an ovenBecause of the terrible famine.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '11: '
      title: 
      number: 11
      content: 'They ravished the women in Zion,  <i>And</i> the maids in the cities
        of Judah.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '12: '
      title: 
      number: 12
      content: 'Princes are hanged up by their hand:The faces of elders were not
        honoured.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '13: '
      title: 
      number: 13
      content: 'They took the young men to grind,And the children fell under the
        wood.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '14: '
      title: 
      number: 14
      content: 'The elders have ceased from the gate,The young men from their musick.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '15: '
      title: 
      number: 15
      content: 'The joy of our heart is ceased;Our dance is turned into mourning.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '16: '
      title: 
      number: 16
      content: 'The crown is fallen <i>from</i> our head:Woe unto us, that we have
        sinned!  '
      comments: []
    - name: '17: '
      title: 
      number: 17
      content: 'For this our heart is faint;For these <i>things</i> our eyes are
        dim.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '18: '
      title: 
      number: 18
      content: 'Because of the mountain of Zion, which is desolate,The foxes walk
        upon it.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '19: '
      title: 
      number: 19
      content: 'Thou, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, remainest for ever;Thy throne
        from generation to generation.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '20: '
      title: 
      number: 20
      content: 'Wherefore dost thou forget us for ever,  <i>And</i> forsake us so
        long time?  '
      comments: []
    - name: '21: '
      title: 
      number: 21
      content: 'Turn thou us unto thee, O <smallcaps>LORD</smallcaps>, and we shall
        be turned;Renew our days as of old.  '
      comments: []
    - name: '22: '
      title: 
      number: 22
      content: But thou hast utterly rejected us;Thou art very wroth against us.
      comments: []
